        <td bgColor="black"><textarea cols="70" name="Message" rows="12" wrap="VIRTUAL">[quote]
The focus items have a bad spread of level range on them.  Level one is for 20 or less, 2 for up to 44 and 3 for up to 60 spells.  Now the items that have 1 or 2 are easily obtainable and common so all levels up to 48 are enjoying thier focus effects for all types. 

 Now what happens when you hit 49?  All your new spells that replaced your 44 and lower ones will no longer be focused.  There are a few items that level 50 ish people can get that have focus 3 effects.  Many of the focus 3 items are only obtainable by uber guilds.  What about the level 49-59 people?  Shouldn't there be some 55ish level items with focus 3 on them?  Verant made it so that from level 49 to 59 you probably won't have any shot of getting the focus 3 item you want.  I'm not saying these items should be easy, but how about putting some on the ToV quest robes etc.  Why not some 55+ loot, not killing NToV or sleepers mobs.  

I think they need to make Focus 3 work up to 55 and Focus 4 work for spells up to 60.  Doesn't make sense to have a gap from 44-60.

 
[/quote]</textarea><br>
